=Description=

"Elizabeth Edwards, wife of former Senator John Edwards, was planning to attend PdF2008 for a keynote conversation about politics, the media, and the impact of the internet on both. But bad weather caused the cancellation of her flights from North Carolina. So we improvised and did the interview by Skype video. About three-quarters of the way in, a surprise guest, her husband, walked by and joined in the conversation. Andrew Rasiej, the co-founder of Personal Democracy Forum, conducted the interview."
